Ford Otosan, Telekom, Turkcell: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-03T07:39:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/ford-otosan-telekom-turkcell-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 45.09, or
0.1 percent, to 58,664.24 yesterday.    Coca-Cola Icecek AS (CCOLA)  : The company that bottles
Coke beverages in Turkey was cut to “neutral” from
“overweight” at JP Morgan Chase & Co., according to a report
today. Coca-Cola Icecek rose 40 kurus, or 2.3 percent, to 17.75
liras.    Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO)  : Ford Motor Co.’s
Turkish joint venture with Koc Holding AS plans to distribute
301.8 million liras ($187 million) of dividends from 2010
profits from April 1. The dividend payout, subject to approval
by shareholders, will be 0.86 liras gross, or 0.7597 liras net
per share, the company said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange  after the market closed yesterday. Ford Otosan gained
15 kurus, or 1.1 percent, to 13.40 liras.    Turk Telekomunikasyon AS (TTKOM)  : Turkey’s biggest
telephony company by sales was reduced to “neutral” from
“outperform” at Credit Suisse Group AG, according to a report
today. Turk Telekom dropped 18 kurus, or 2.5 percent, to 6.98
liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Turkey’s
biggest mobile phone company was cut to “underperform” from
“outperform” at Credit Suisse. Turkcell declined 14 kurus, or
1.6 percent, to 8.58 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
